Title: No van Dam-Veltman-Zakharov Discontinuity for Supergravity in AdS Space
Authors: P.A. Grassi (New York Univ.) and P. van Nieuwenhuizen (YITP, Stony
  Brook)
Comments: November 2000, 7pp, misprints and typos corrected
Report-no: YITP-00-78, NYU-TH/00/11/03
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B499 (2001) 174-178
\\
  Adding explicit mass terms for the spin 2 and spin 3/2 field of N=1 anti-de
Sitter supergravity, the limit M --> 0 for these mass terms is smooth: there is
no van Dam-Veltman-Zakharov mass discontinuity in the propagators when the
cosmological constant is non-vanishing.
